Product Description


About Product

  • Cultar, a plant growth regulator (PGR) manufactured by Syngenta, is designed to regulate plant growth effectively.
  • Cultar Syngenta technical name - Paclobutrazole 23% Sc
  • As a systemic PGR, it is absorbed by the plant and transported throughout its tissues.
  • It acts by inhibiting the production of gibberellins, which are plant hormones responsible for promoting cell elongation and growth.

Cultar Syngenta Plant Growth Regulator Technical Details

  • Composition:

    Component Content (% W/W)
    Paclobutrazol 23
    Alkylated Napthalene Sulphonate 3.0
    Xanthangum 0.03
    Sodium bentonite/Aluminum Silicate 2.5
    Polydimethyl Siloxanes+Silica 0.3
    Benzisothiazolin-3-one 0.01
    Propylene glycol 5.0

  • Mode of Action: Cultar Syngenta plant growth regulator works by blocking the production of gibberellins, which are plant hormones that stimulate growth. When gibberellins are blocked, the plant’s growth is reduced. This results in a denser plant with smaller leaves and fruits.

Key Features and Benefits

  • By controlling vegetative growth, Cultar makes plants more compact and enhances their fruit quality.
  • Cultar Syngenta Plant Growth Regulator boosts fruit size, colour, and yield by regulating plant growth.
  • It helps plants to flower and set fruit earlier by inhibiting vegetative growth.
  • It saves time and labour costs by reducing the need for pruning.
  • Increases plant tolerance to pests and diseases by controlling vegetative growth.
